  "text": "To investigate the stability of the new type of traveling waves, we conducted a series of numerical simulations, since in general it is quite difficult to check stability of traveling waves analytically [CITATION_1] . For a given applied stress σ, we used the Verlet algorithm (a symplectic scheme [CITATION_2] ) to solve the system (1) of ordinary differential equation for a truncated lattice with N masses, ranging from N = 600 to 2000, depending on the time of the simulation. A longer chain was used if the simulation ran for a long time, in order to avoid reflection of elastic waves from the domain boundaries. The boundary conditions were u 0 = σ + 1 and u N = σ − 1. Two types of initial conditions were used. The first one was Riemann-type piecewise constant initial displacement and zero initial velocity:",
